Ad Text:
Senior Data Scientist for Artificial Intelligence Team | Fixed Term Contract

Are you a technically strong Data Scientist who enjoys solving complex problems end-to-end from experimentation through to production?

This company are building advanced AI capability within their organisation and are looking for a Senior Data Scientist to help design, deploy, and operationalise cutting-edge machine learning solutions across the business.

This is not a research only role. This is real world AI in production.

The Opportunity

You'll work across the full breadth of modern data science, including:

Natural Language Processing (NLP) & LLM applications
Time-series forecasting & anomaly detection
Computer vision & speech technologies
IoT and sensor data modelling
Statistical modelling and advanced ML algorithms
Cloud-native deployment (Azure environment preferred)

You'll take ownership of projects from concept through to deployment, collaborating with Infrastructure and Operations teams to ensure solutions are robust, scalable, and production-ready.

What You'll Be Doing

Design, build and deploy ML/AI models in managed cloud environments
Develop NLP solutions (NER, sentiment analysis, text classification, topic modelling, clustering, document understanding)
Apply specialised modelling techniques including geospatial analytics and time-series forecasting
Productionise models using MLOps best practices (CI/CD for ML)
Work across SQL/NoSQL data stores and ETL/ELT workflows
Communicate insights and progress clearly with business stakeholders
Contribute to innovation and technical direction within the AI function

What We're Looking For

4+ years' experience developing and deploying data science or AI models
Strong grounding in statistics and machine learning algorithms
Experience working with NLP and/or LLM technologies
Proficiency in Python (NumPy, pandas, SciPy, scikit-learn)
Experience deploying ML solutions in Azure (or similar cloud platforms)
Data engineering experience
Practical exposure to MLOps and model productionisation
Strong stakeholder communication skills

Why Join?

End-to-end technical ownership
Work on advanced AI problems not just dashboards
Exposure to diverse modelling domains (NLP, CV, IoT, time-series)
Opportunity to help shape and grow AI capability
Collaborative, forward thinking technology environment

If you're passionate about applying first-principles thinking to real operational challenges and want to see your models deployed at scale, we'd love to hear from you.

Location: Melbourne / Brisbane / Sydney
Role type: Full time / Fixed Term Contact

Enjoy a range of exclusive benefits, including discounted private health insurance, salary packaging options, access to Fitness Passport, lifestyle and travel discounts, access to I-MED services for you and your family, as well as comprehensive employee assistance and wellbeing programs.

About the role

I-MED Radiology is seeking two Data Engineer's to design, build and maintain scalable data pipelines and platforms that enable access to high-quality, reliable data across the organisation.

Reporting to the Data and Integrations Manager, this role will be a key member of the IT Services team responsible for implementing best-practice data engineering standards, ensuring data security and governance, and delivering robust technical solutions that support I-MED's clinical, operational and commercial decision-making.

You'll work closely with a broad range of stakeholders across business units, including IT Managers, Operations, Commercial, Marketing and external partners, to continuously improve data infrastructure, tooling and processes.

Key responsibilities

Design, build and maintain scalable, high-performing data pipelines and platforms
Develop automated data ingestion, transformation and loading processes
Optimise pipelines for performance, reliability and cost efficiency
Implement monitoring, alerting and lifecycle management for data workflows
Contribute to data architecture and modelling aligned with business requirements
Ensure compliance with I-MED security policies and governance frameworks
Collaborate effectively with internal stakeholders, clinicians and IT peers
Diagnose and resolve data pipeline issues and drive continuous improvement
Contribute to shared engineering standards, documentation and reusable components

About you

Tertiary qualification in a relevant or related field
Experience with the Amazon Web Services (AWS) data stack and related technologies
Proficiency in Python and SQL
Strong understanding of data ingestion patterns, modelling and platform architectures
Experience working with healthcare data, integration standards (HL7, DICOM) and healthcare integration engines
Knowledge of software engineering best practices and DevOps principles
Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills
Strong analytical and problem-solving mindset with attention to detail

Why I-MED?

Work with modern data technologies supporting clinical and operational excellence
Be part of a large, purpose-driven healthcare network delivering real impact
Drive data engineering maturity and innovation at scale across a national business
Collaborate with leading experts in technology, radiology and healthcare analytics

Interstate travel may be required.

Apply now to play a key role in shaping the future of data and analytics at I-MED Radiology.

GRIT is hiring on behalf of our client in the AEC sector for a skilled Machine Learning Engineer with strong Python expertise and experience delivering within larger, cross-functional teams. In this role, you’ll play a key part in designing, developing, and deploying ML models and AI-driven solutions on Azure, collaborating closely with BAs, developers, and data professionals to support innovation across the built environment.

What You’ll Do

Design, develop, and deploy machine learning models into production environments
Collaborate with analysts, engineers, and business stakeholders to transform prototypes into scalable solutions
Enhance MLOps pipelines and ensure performance, reliability, and accuracy
Leverage Azure ML, AI Search, OpenAI and cloud-based data services
Monitor, update and maintain ML models to ensure optimal performance
What you’ll bring:
1+ year of commercial experience in machine learning and Python
Solid grasp of tools like scikit-learn, pandas, NumPy, matplotlib, Plotly
Experience working in production environments with Git and cloud (Azure preferred)
Proficiency in Python (using VSCode or PyCharm)
Strong problem-solving, time management, and communication skills
A degree in Computer Science, Data Science, Engineering or related field
Azure ML experience or certification highly desirable
Highly Desirable:
Knowledge of MLOps (MLFlow, Optuna), REST APIs (FastAPI, Flask), and Linux
Experience with PyTorch or TensorFlow
Familiarity with 3D geometry or IFC/IfcOpenShell
This is a fast moving role! Reach out to TJ Tan on +61489279874 or tj@grittalent.com for a confidential discussion.

We’ve partnered with an exciting start-up who are hiring a Lead AI Engineer to own the design, delivery, and performance of production AI systems inside a fast-growing SaaS company. This is a hands-on leadership role for someone who sets technical direction, builds critical components themselves, and raises the standard across the team.

The Role
You’ll lead the architecture and execution of AI features embedded in a data-rich platform. You’ll partner closely with product and engineering, translate ambition into scalable systems, and ensure everything shipped is reliable, secure, and cost-efficient.

Key Responsibilities
• Own AI technical strategy and architecture
• Build and ship production-grade AI systems end to end
• Design reliable retrieval and multi-step AI workflows
• Establish strong AI-ready data models and contracts
• Implement evaluation frameworks and production monitoring
• Optimise for cost, latency, scalability, and reliability
• Enforce privacy and security-by-design standards
• Mentor engineers and drive technical excellence

What You Bring
• Strong backend engineering background with experience shipping production systems
• Proven technical leadership and ownership across teams
• Hands-on experience with LLM systems (RAG, tool calling, orchestration workflows, prompt management, model routing)
• Strong data systems capability (SQL, APIs, structured data modelling)
• Experience building reliable, observable, high-performance systems
• Clear communication and the ability to align stakeholders around technical decisions

What’s On Offer
• Flexible working arrangements
• High ownership and autonomy
• A smart, collaborative team environment
• Direct impact on a growing SaaS product’s AI capability

If you want to lead from the front and build AI systems that customers rely on every day, this is that role.

As an Automation Engineer, you will be working as part of a team on larger programs, you will be supporting client relationships and being the point of contact for project-related activities. You should be able to build and maintain strong relationships with clients and be able to collaborate effectively with other stakeholders, including project teams, subject-matter experts, and business users.

Automation Engineers are focused on developing Intelligent Automation solutions, e.g., RPA, IDP, Test Automation, BPM (especially workflow and/or process orchestration), and Conv. AI. Experience in software development (Java, Python, as well as VB.NET)

Responsibilities & tasks for this role

Perform system analysis, design, implement, test, enhance, support, and document enterprise automation platforms with automation technologies.

Consult our clients providing advice, guidance and expertise in the professional and technical implementation of intelligent process automation solutions with focus on RPA, cognitive computing, and artificial intelligence (AI).

Develop end-to-end automation solutions and continuous improvement strategies that drive efficiencies, improve processes, and deliver tangible business outcomes in order to address complex business problems with a deep understanding of the automation technology landscape.

Prepare and support client presentations and workshops.

Support the Account Manager in the development of client relationships and development of proposals.

Support the conceptual development of our Delivery team within Roboyo.

Must-have qualifications & competencies

Minimum of 3 years of experience in automation (UiPath, Microsoft Power Platform)

UiPath certifications are desirable

Strong track record of project management and data analysis

Knowledgeable in at least one area of consulting, such as strategy, transformation, digitization, or technology.

Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to think strategically and creatively

Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to build and maintain strong client relationships

Job Title: MSP - L2 Support and L3 Systems Engineers - M365/Azure - Award-Winning MSPs!
Ad Text:
Saul Recruitment - Specialising in recruiting top MSP talent across Oz & NZ!
  
Melbourne | $80k–$140k + Super + Training | Flexible WFH Options :-)
  
Join some of Australia’s most reputable, multi-branch MSPs – genuine local success stories with a trophy cabinet to prove it. These guys are growing fast, setting the standard, and building teams that thrive on collaboration, innovation and delivering real impact.
  
Why you’ll love it:

Cutting-edge projects – from cloud migrations to complex BAU, no two days are the same.
Supportive leadership – management that listens, guides, and invests in you.
Career growth – structured training, certifications and clear progression pathways.
Hybrid working – flexibility to balance office and home.
Team spirit – highly skilled engineers who share knowledge and lift each other up.  
This is more than a job – it’s a chance to be part of some of Australia's most dynamic MSPs that challenge the status quo, rewards initiative, and celebrates people who step up.
  
What you’ll be doing

Level 2 technical support and sys administration across multiple client environments for managed service customers
Project delivery (relevant for L3 Role) – especially cloud migrations and transformation projects!
Troubleshoot, diagnose, resolve or escalate complex issues
On-site client visits (you’ll be the face of the team at times)
Document and improve processes, always looking for better ways to do things
Jump into senior project work as needed – variety guaranteed
What you’ll bring

Prior MSP experience across a mix of: Windows, M365, Azure, On-Prem, Intune, Azure Virtualisation, Backup & DR, Networking, Security, Scripting
Happy to be “hands & feet” on site when required
Great communicator – written and verbal – with a friendly, customer-focused approach
Organised, adaptable, and able to juggle priorities in a fast-paced environment
A genuine team player who wants to contribute, learn and grow
  
What’s in it for you?
  
✔ Work with one of Australia’s most trusted, award-winning MSPs
✔ Be mentored by some of the sharpest engineers in the game
✔ Access ongoing training, certifications and development opportunities
✔ Exposure to emerging technologies you’ll want on your CV
✔ A truly collaborative, open culture that values people as much as outcomes
  
This is a real opportunity to shine – and to be recognised and rewarded for it.
  
$2000 Referral Bonus: Know someone perfect? Refer them and score $2000 if they’re successful! Feel free to use the dedicated referral link on my site :-)
